The paper deals with low-rank matrix approximation, which is a topic in both information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithms presented in the paper involve linear algebraic operations, which is a common theme in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the optimality of the trade-off between the number of columns and the approximation ratio, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents algorithms with computational complexity analysis, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SI).
